        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 5:27PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms near Melstone and 17 miles northeast of Melstone,
moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Melstone.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
